Jackpot Enterprises to sell casino . Jackpot Enterprises Inc said it reached a letter of intent to sell one of its two remaining casinos . It did not disclose the planned buyer or ther terms of the deal , but said it expected to have a definitive agreement by the end of November . It said the sale will allow it to focus on its core gaming machine business , and other strategic opportunities . " The increase in gaming machine route operations revenues reflects progress in gaining new accounts and new store openings for existing chain stores , " Jackpot president and chief executive officer Don Kornstein said in a statement . But he also said the company sees a lot of its future growth coming from investments in " attractive , value - oriented non - gaming opportunities . " He added that " while the gaming machine route business generates relatively stable cash flows , it is not a high growth business . " 
